					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Books IV-VI of Maimonides' Mishneh Torah, with glosses in the style of the Tosafists, followed by Meir of Rothenburg's responses on the subject of the same books. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="200v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Mishneh Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">משנה תורה</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/89860273">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/89860273" xml:lang="en">Meir ben Baruch, of Rothenburg, approximately 1215-1293 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/89860273" xml:lang="he">מאיר בן ברוך, מרוטנבורג, -1293 </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The enumeration of the mitsṿot is given at the beginning of each book. At the end of book VI (folio 177r) a list of all the halakhot is added. </p>
								<p>Most of the halakhic decisions appended at the end of the volume are signed by Meir ben Barukh [of Rothenburg]. The names of Isaac ben Samuel, Isaac ben Moses, Isaac ben Avraham, Samuel ben Avraham, Samson ben Avraham stand respectively at the end of some of the responses. </p>
								<p>This manuscript, as well as Add. 11438, was probably copied (by persons of learning) from codices prepared by pupils of Meir of Rothenburg. It is possible that this manuscript was the codex from which Add. 11438 was copied. </p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. Add MS 11438, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">495</ref>.</filiation>
