					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>200 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>325</height>
										<width>225</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>235</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>200 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). Folio 1 is a moden paper flyleaf, folio 199 and 200 are paper slips belonging to the 17th or 18th century. </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 8 leaves each (the last quires is missing one leaf). </p>
									<p>There are catchwords at the end of the quires. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained. </p>
									<p>Margins slightly damaged. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="41 59" writtenLines="41 59">
									<p>In folio 2v-12r, 179r-199v each page is divided into 2 columns, with 50-59 lines in a full column. The pages contained in folios 12v-178v, which are undivided, have 41 or 42 lines each. </p>
									<p>Pricking and plummet ruling (each bifolio on both sides) is visible. Hair-side and flesh-side of folios indistinguishable. </p>
									<p>Chapter numbers given in larger characters. The main text is given in larger characters and the comments are in smaller characters. </p>
									<p>Occasional marginal notes and additions. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Short notes in a 14th or 15th century Ashkenazi hand: folio 198v (only upper part of leaf is preserved, otherwise blank). </p>
							<p>A small octavo paper leaf with notes:  folio199. </p>
							<p>Folio 200: a small leaf containing some Ashkenazi notes on one side, which mention a certain rabi Bendit and his father Gershon. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. Harley coat of arms on the upper and lower covers. </p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Maimonides. Mishneh Thorah. Books IV &amp; VI. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harl. Or. 5702.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
